com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.server
Interface Server

All Superinterfaces:
com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.Capability, com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.DeployModelObject, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Implementing Classes:
ServerImpl
public interface Server
extends com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.Capability

A representation of the model object 'Server'.

The following features are supported:

  • Auto Start
  • Cpu Architecture
  • Cpu Count
  • Cpu Architecture Width
  • Cpu Cores Installed
  • Cpu Dies Installed
  • Cpu Manufacturer
  • Cpu Speed
  • Cpu Type
  • Is VMI Dan LPAR
  • Manufacturer
  • Memory Size
  • Model
  • Primary MAC Address
  • Processing Capacity
  • Processing Capacity Units
  • Rom Version
  • Serial Number
  • System Board UUID
  • System Id
  • Virtual
  • Vmid

See Also:
ServerPackage.getServer()

isAutoStart

boolean isAutoStart()
Returns the value of the 'Auto Start' attribute.

If the meaning of the 'Auto Start' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

In the circumstances where the Computer System environment supports this function (such as in Virtualization), AutoStart represents whether or not the instance is automatically started under particular circumstances. These circumstances could include when the ComputerSystem is powered off, it will automatically restart when power is restored to the machine. Another circumstance includes when virtual computer system instances are automatically started when the physcial computer system instance is started.

Returns:
the value of the 'Auto Start' attribute.

getManufacturer

java.lang.String getManufacturer()
Returns the value of the 'Manufacturer' attribute.

If the meaning of the 'Manufacturer' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

The string for the manufacturer should match the strings defined in the following URL: http://www.iana.org/assignments/enterprise-numbers In addition to the names on the list, there are a few corrections and extensions due to mergers, acquisitions, etc. The following is a list of currently defined changes to the URL above. "42", "Sun Microsystems" "1872", "Nortel Networks (Alteon)" "1916", "Extreme" "Other" "Other" is a valid string that applications can use if the application manufacturer string has not been defined in the URL above. Manufacturers that are not on the list should contact the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA) to get an assigned number. Applications placing data in the Common Data Model are responsible for mapping application manufacturer strings to strings defined in the URL above. For example, applications need to use "IBM" as a manufacturer string and not "International Business Machines", "IBM Corp", "IBM Corporation", "International Business Machines Corporation", etc.

Returns:
the value of the 'Manufacturer' attribute.
See Also:
setManufacturer(String), ServerPackage.getServer_Manufacturer()

isVirtual

boolean isVirtual()
Returns the value of the 'Virtual' attribute.

If the meaning of the 'Virtual' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

Boolean. Set to true if this is a virtual computer system. This flag should be set regardless of how the virtualization is implemented (Hardware - pSeries and ZSeries, OperatingSystem - VMWareESX, Application - VMWare).

Returns:
the value of the 'Virtual' attribute.

getVmid

java.lang.String getVmid()
Returns the value of the 'Vmid' attribute.

If the meaning of the 'Vmid' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

The VMID is a unique identifier for the virtual machine. For pSeries this is the LPARID. pSeries boxex can have multiple LPARS running different operating systems. The pSeries implementation will return the same manufacturer, model, and serial number all the LPARs. So all ComputerSystems running in different LPARs end up getting incorrectly merged down to a single object. In order to avoid this merging in a pSeries environment, the LPARID shoiuld be saved in the VMID attribute.

Returns:
the value of the 'Vmid' attribute.
See Also:
setVmid(String), ServerPackage.getServer_Vmid()
